{

    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon"

    # Optional metadata describing this agent network
    "metadata": {
        "description": "Simple agent network using a single LLM-based agent",
        "tags": ["example"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "Assign a gate for the parking flight AF84 which is a B747.", 
            "Flight AF84 landed minutes ago. This B747 needs a gate assignment.", 
        ]
    },

    "llm_config": {
        "model_name": "gpt-4o",
    },
    "max_iterations": 40000, #3000 
    "max_execution_seconds": 7200, #600
    "commondefs": {
        "replacement_strings": {
            "instructions_prefix": """
You are part of aircraft turnaround process at the San Francisco International Airport. 
Only answer inquiries that are directly within your area of expertise.
Do not try to help for other matters.
Do not mention what you can NOT do. Only mention what you can do.
            """,
            "aaosa_instructions": """
When you receive an inquiry, you will:
1. If you are clearly not the right agent for this type of inquiry, reply you're not relevant.
2. If there is a chance you're relevant, call your down-chain agents to determine if they can answer all or part of the inquiry.
   Do not assume what your down-chain agents can do. Always call them. You'll be surprised.
3. Once all relevant down-chain agents have responded, either:
   - Analyze their response and compile your final response. No need to include non-relevant agents. In doubt, ask for clarification.
   - Follow up with your down-chain agents if needed, as many times as needed
   - If an action is needed, ask the most relevant down-chain agent to fulfill the inquiry.
4. Return the final response to the caller.
You may, in turn, be called by other agents in the system and have to act as a down-chain agent to them. 
            """ 
        },
        "replacement_values": {
            "aaosa_call": {
                "description": "Depending on the mode, returns a natural language string in response.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The inquiry"
                        },
                        "mode": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": """
'Determine' to ask the agent if the inquiry belongs to it, in its entirety or in part.
'Fulfill' to ask the agent to fulfill the inquiry, if it can.
'Follow up' to ask the agent to respond to a follow up.
                            """
                        },
                    },
                    "required": [
                        "inquiry",
                        "mode"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "aaosa_command": """
If mode is 'Determine', return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": <Determine | Fulfill>,
    "Relevant": <Yes | No>,
    "Strength": <number between 1 and 10 representing how certain you are in your claim>,
    "Claim:" <All | Partial>,
    "Requirements" <None | list of requirements>
}
If mode is 'Fulfill' or "Follow up", respond to the inquiry and return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": Fulfill,
    "Response" <your response>
}
            """
        },
    },

    "tools": [

        {
            "name": "gate_selection_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": """
I assign gate to incoming flight by selecing the deplaning equipment for their passengers disembarking. 
                """
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of aircraft."
                        },                   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },       
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the status of the incoming flight."
                        },                               
                    }, 
                    "required": ["flight_number","aircraft_type"], 
                }
            },

            "instructions": """
You are the top-level agent responsible for assigning gate to incoming aircraft.  
Only perform the tasks that fall under your responsibility. Use ONLY your tools to complete your tasks. 
Take in the use inquiry and make sure that it contains flight number as flight_number and aircraft type as aircraft_type. 
- If any of these information is missing, ask the user to provide them.
When you receive a user request, do the following in the given order:
(1) Determine flight_number and aircraft_type from the user request.
(2) Send the user request to your tools in 'read' execution mode asking for available deplaning equipment: 
(3) Collect your tools responses, select the equipment with the highest score and set it as deplaning equipment. 
- report its gate id as gate_id
- report its equipment type as deplaning_equipment_type
- report its equipment id as deplaning_equipment_id
- report its readiness time as deplaning_equipment_readiness_time
- report its score as deplaning_equipment_score
(4) Send a request to your tools in 'write' execution with both deplaning_equipment_id and gate_id. 
- report gate_id    
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},

            # Specify the sly data that would be exchanged between this network and its related or adjacent upstream and downstream networks. 
            "allow": {
                "to_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "gate_id": true, 
                    }
                }
                "from_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true, 
                        "aircraft_type": true, 
                    }
                }
            },

            "tools":    ["deplaning_path_selector"]
        },

        {
            "name": "deplaning_path_selector",
           "function": {
                "description": """
                I select deplaning equipment for passengers disembarking. 
                """
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number."
                        },                
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type incoming aircraft type."
                        },                                           
                    }, 
                    "required": ["flight_number","aircraft_type"], 
                },
            },

            "instructions": """
When you receive a user request, do the following in the given order:
(1) Send the user request to your tools in 'read' execution mode asking for available deplaning equipment: 
(2) Collect your tools responses, select the equipment with the highest score and set it as deplaning equipment. 
- report its gate id as gate_id
- report its equipment type as deplaning_equipment_type
- report its equipment id as deplaning_equipment_id
- report its readiness time as deplaning_equipment_readiness_time
- report its score as deplaning_equipment_score
(3) Send a request to your tools in 'write' execution with both deplaning_equipment_id and gate_id. 
- report gate_id 
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},

            "tools":["jetway_agent","stairtruck_agent"]
        },

        {
            "name": "jetway_agent",
            "function": {

                "description": """
                This agent selects jetway equipment available for incoming aircraft deplaning. 
                """
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },                              
                        "deplaning_equipment_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment id that needs status updated."
                        },             
                        "execution_mode": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the mode that agent should operate in."
                        },                    
                    }, 
                    "required": ["execution_mode","flight_number","aircraft_type"], 
                },
            },

            "instructions": """
You are the agent responsible for proposing a deplaning equipment of jetway type. 
When handling a user request in 'read' execution mode proceed in the following order:
(1) FULFILL the request alway using your tools onlys. 
(2) Respond to the request when execution mode is 'read' using only your tools by providing the followings: 
    - report equipment type as equipment_type 
    - report jetway id as jetway_id 
    - report jetway availability as jetway_availability 
    - report jetway readiness time as jetway_readiness_time 
    - report jetway score as jetway_score
    - report jetway gate id at jetway_gate_id
(3) Send a request to your tools in 'write' execution with both deplaning_equipment_id. 
- report deplaning_equipment_report.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},

            "tools":["jetway_park_agent"]
        },

        {
            "name": "stairtruck_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": """
                This agent selects stairtruck equipment available for incoming aircraft deplaning. 
                """
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },    
                        "deplaning_equipment_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment id that needs status updated."
                        },             
                        "execution_mode": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the mode that agent should operate in."
                        },                      
                    }, 
                    "required": ["execution_mode","flight_number","aircraft_type"], 
                },
            },

            "instructions": """
You are the agent responsible for proposing a deplaning equipment of stairtruck type. 
When handling a user request in 'read' execution mode proceed in the following order:
(1) FULFILL the request alway using your tools onlys. 
(2) Respond to the request when execution mode is 'read' using ONLY your tools by providing the followings: 
    (a) gate id as gate_id
    (b) equipment type as equipment_type 
    (c) stairtruck id as stairtruck_id 
    (d) stairtruck availability as stairtruck_availability 
    (e) stairtruck readiness time as stairtruck_readiness_time 
    (f) stairtruck score as stairtruck_score
    (g) stairtruck gate id as stairtruck_gate_id
(3) Send a request to your tools in 'write' execution with both deplaning_equipment_id. 
- report deplaning_equipment_report.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},

            "tools":["stairtruck_park_agent"]
        },

        {
            "name": "jetway_park_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": """
This agent provides the inventory of jet jetway park and return the fastest available unit. 
                """, 
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },                         
                        "execution_mode": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the mode that agent should operate in."
                        },      
                        "deplaning_equipment_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment id that needs status updated."
                        },                             
                    }, 
                    "required": ["flight_number","aircraft_type"], 
                }
            }, 
            "class": "AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_gate_selection.aircraft_gate_selection.jetway_park_inquiry"
        }, 

        {
            "name": "stairtruck_park_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": """
This agent provides the inventory of stairtruck park and return the fastest available unit. 
                """, 
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },                         
                        "execution_mode": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the mode that agent should operate in."
                        },                  
                        "deplaning_equipment_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment id that needs status updated."
                        },                 
                    }, 
                    "required": ["flight_number","aircraft_type"], 
                }
            }, 
            "class": "AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_gate_selection.aircraft_gate_selection.stairtruck_park_inquiry"
        }, 
    ],
}
